snippet: A penthouse duplex at the HL23 condominium at the High Line is listed for $22.95 million. The seller is Pierre Lagrange, one of Britain’s richest men.
abstract: Duplex penthouse hanging over Chelsea's High Line is being listed by British hedge fund manager Pierre Lagrange for $22.95 million, over double what he paid for it.
lead_paragraph: A penthouse duplex at the HL23 condominium at the High Line is listed for $22.95 million. The seller is Pierre Lagrange, one of Britain’s richest men.
